# personal-id-forbidden.regex
#
# Patterns that MUST NOT appear in any shipped framework artefact
# (cli/, skills/, agents/, commands/, templates/, scripts/, dev-tools/,
# CLAUDE.md, README.md, docs/).
#
# Format: one extended-regex pattern per non-empty, non-comment line.
# Lines starting with `#` are comments. Each pattern is matched
# case-insensitively via perl -CSD (UTF-8-safe; BSD-compatible).
#
# Inline exclusion fence: lines between
#   <!-- gate:example-only -->
# and
#   <!-- /gate:example-only -->
# are exempt (counter-examples and teaching content).
#
# Consumers may extend this by pointing --regex at their own merged file.
# Do NOT add ecosystem-specific entries here — keep the framework contract
# neutral. Consumer extensions belong in the consumer's local copy.

# Operator personal handles / names (word-boundary, case-insensitive)
\bpavel\b
\bvalentov\b
\bpaxbeach\b
\byuval\b

# Ecosystem-specific hostnames / project names
\barcana-dev\b

# Ecosystem-specific Vault/credential paths
arcanada/aether

# Personal Asana PAT variable names (any ASANA_*_PAT pattern)
ASANA_[A-Z_]*PAT

# 16-digit numeric IDs (Asana workspace/user GIDs)
\b[0-9]{16}\b
